KEY GOVERNANCE BODIES:

1. EXECUTIVE STEERING COMMITTEE
   вҖў Frequency: Monthly
   вҖў Chair: Chief Digital Officer
   вҖў Members: Department heads, Sponsor, Finance lead
   вҖў Purpose: Strategic decisions, budget approval, executive escalation
   вҖў Authority: Can override project decisions if needed

2. DIGITAL GOVERNANCE BOARD
   вҖў Frequency: Bi-weekly
   вҖў Chair: Digital Governance Manager
   вҖў Members: CDO, IT Security, Data Protection Officer, Project Manager
   вҖў Purpose: Compliance, risk, policy alignment
   вҖў Authority: Approve governance policies; escalate issues

3. PROJECT DELIVERY STEERING COMMITTEE
   вҖў Frequency: Weekly
   вҖў Chair: Project Sponsor
   вҖў Members: Project Manager, Dept. representatives, Tech Lead
   вҖў Purpose: Day-to-day project oversight; milestone tracking
   вҖў Authority: Approve project phases; manage scope changes

4. COMPLIANCE & RISK COMMITTEE
   вҖў Frequency: Bi-weekly
   вҖў Chair: IT Security Officer
   вҖў Members: Data Protection Officer, Compliance Manager, Risk Officer
   вҖў Purpose: Risk management, security, compliance review
   вҖў Authority: Approve security/compliance controls; audit findings

5. TECHNICAL & SECURITY REVIEW BOARD
   вҖў Frequency: As needed (critical milestones)
   вҖў Chair: IT Security Officer
   вҖў Members: Technical Lead, Security Architect, Integration Lead
   вҖў Purpose: Technical architecture, security assessment, integration review
   вҖў Authority: Approve technical designs; authorize deployments
